# ğŸ¥ clinicalNLP  
### Clinical Documentation Intelligence & Utilization Review System  

clinicalNLP is a production-oriented NLP system that transforms unstructured emergency department (ER) documentation into structured, severity-aware clinical intelligence.

The system combines rule-based medical signal extraction with large language model reasoning to generate audit-aligned, structured outputs suitable for utilization review workflows.

---

## ğŸš€ Core Capabilities  

### ğŸ“„ Clinical Document Ingestion
- PDF upload (ER notes, admission notes)
- Structured text extraction
- Section parsing (HPI, Vitals, Labs, Imaging, Assessment)

---

### ğŸ§  Medical Signal Extraction
- Diagnosis detection  
- Vital sign abnormality detection  
- Lab abnormality flagging  
- Organ dysfunction heuristics  
- Hypoxia detection  
- Severity stratification  

---

### ğŸ¤– LLM Reasoning Layer  

Model used:

```
Llama-3.3-70B-Versatile
```

The LLM functions as a structured reasoning engine to:

- Synthesize clinical severity  
- Differentiate moderate vs critical instability  
- Generate admission-level justification summaries  
- Maintain consistent, schema-validated outputs  

The LLM layer is abstracted behind a service module and operates within a deterministic pipeline.

---

